author: news24.com
title: Myanmar wants election postponed due to flooding
text:
Bangkok - Myanmar's Election Commission said it wants to postpone next month's general election due to natural disasters, local media said on Tuesday.
The commission urged the major political parties to agree to postpone elections due to pervasive flooding and landslides throughout the country, the Myanmar Times newspaper said.
Four parties agreed to the postponement, including the ruling army-backed Union Solidarity and Development Party. But the main opposition National League for Democracy refused to accept the delay.
The election commission has not yet announced a final decision.
